MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS deep spot for Amox Lake.  The site is 0.5 kilometers west of Elm Road on the Amox Lake access road
The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS deep spot for Bealeau Lake.  The lake is accessed from the Oak Lane boat landing on Koonz Lake.
The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS deep spot for Circle of Flight Project 1.  The site is 3 meters North of National Guard Rd.
The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS deep spot for Circle of Flight Project 2.  The site is 0.4 km Northeast of the Circle of Flight sign on West Town Hall Road.

The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS location for the Embarrass River.  The site is 100 meters South of Highway A.  Take the fire truck path to the dry hydrant next to the ponds.  Head west in the barren field to the forest edge.  Sample directly below the confluence of Henning Creek and the North Branch of the Embarrass River.
The FY2004 site is used to display QA/QC samples that were collected in the field.
The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS deep spot for Island Lake.  The site is accessed at Captain Cove's Resort.
The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS deep spot for Koonz Lake.  The site is accessed from the boat landing on Oak Ridge Rd.  Koonz Lake is connected to Beauleau Lake by canal
`The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS deep spot for Malone Lake.  The site is located North of the Hurt residence, which is North of Highway VV.`

`The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS location for Miller Creek 1.  The site is located 100 meters North of Anderson Road.  The bedrock creates a fairly uniform section, which is used for flow measurements.  Invertebrate samples are taken below the flow site and samples are taken above the flow site.`

`The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS location for Miller Creek 2.  The site is located directly above County Highway G.  Stream flow is measured underneath the bridge and invertebrate, water, hydrolab samples are taken North of the bridge.`
The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS deep spot for Mission Lake.  The site is 10 meters South of County Highway G next to the Mission church.
The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS location for Mill Creek.  The site is 200 meters Southwest of Amox Lake along Quinney logging road.  The site is 2 kilometers Southwest of Elm Road.

MonitoringLocationName: East Branch of the Red River 1
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: `The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS deep spot for the East Branch of the Red River 1.  The flow, invertebrate, hydrolab and water sampling sites are directly south of National Guard Road.`

MonitoringLocationName: East Branch of the Red River 2
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS deep spot for the East Branch of the Red River 2.  The invertebrate site is directly North of Besaw's bridge on River Road.  Sample the first run North of the bridge.  Flow is taken at the old wooden framework farther to the North along the east side of the river.  The Hydrolab and water samples are collected North of the flow site.

The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS location for the East Branch of the Red River Gage Station.  The site is South of West Town Hall Road directly behind Greg Millers residence.  Flow is taken from the gage station.  Invertebrates are collected in the run/riffle to the West of the gage station.  Water samples and the Hydrolab data are collected directly south of the Gage Station intake pipe.
`The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS deep spot for Silver Creek.  The flow, water sample, hydrolab and invertebrate samples are collected directly at the first riffle East of Silver Creek Road.`

The site is the FY2007 GIS based GPS location on Smith Creek.  The site is directly east of the culvert and forest road crossing.  Flow and chemistry is taken directly downstream of the culvert.  The stream is heavily impacted by past beaver activity.  The substrate is primarily sediment.  A large amount of woody debris is laid down in the channel.  The shoreline above the site is wooded.  A grassy flooded plain occurs below the site.

`The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS site location for the Tributary to Smith Creek.  The site is one kilometer east of Camp 14 on the logging road North of Smith Creek.  The site has been sample errouneously.  The flow location is below the culvert.  Water samples, invertebrates and the hydrolab are collected above the culvert.`
The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS deep spot for Upper Red Lake.  The site is 300 meters Southwest of Upper Red Lake road

MonitoringLocationName: West Branch of the Red River 1
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: `The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS location for the West Branch of the Red River 1.  The site is 100 meters West of Moh he con nuck Road.  Flow, water samples and the hydrolab data are measured below the swimming hole and above the small man made dam.  Invertebrates are collected below the dam.`

MonitoringLocationName: West Branch of the Red River 2
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: `The site is the FY2004 WAAS enabled GPS location for the West Branch of the Red River 2.  The site is directly West of Murphy's Rd.  Flow is measured immediately West of the Bridge and invertebrates, water samples and the hydrolab are taken from the runs approximately 10 meters west of the bridge.`
